🧩 4. Production Engine (Turns Jobs Into Output)

production.py

class ProductionEngine:
    def produce(self, agent, town):
        job = agent.get_job()
        if not job:
            return

        # Check input resources
        for res, amt in job.input_resources.items():
            if town.resources[res].quantity < amt:
                return  # can't produce

        # Consume inputs
        for res, amt in job.input_resources.items():
            town.resources[res].quantity -= amt

        # Produce outputs
        for res, amt in job.output_resources.items():
            town.resources[res].quantity += amt

This is the *economic heartbeat* of each town.
